Attack Characterization¶

How we define attacks determines how we label the .csv. Pentesting machine: 10.10.10.19. Traffic after sliding window source port 56934 is malicious when sent from x.x.x.19 to x.x.x.11

Notice that solely using the Source IP address mislabels 15 rows of flow to the DC. Do these 15 rows count because the malicious IP is asking the DC where things are on the network via DNS?

# Define malicious criteria. Here it is the following IP address:
def bad(x):
    if x == '10.10.10.19':
        return 1
    else:
        return 0
In [7]:
# Apply the criteria to a new column called 'label'
df['Label'] = df['Src IP'].apply(bad)
